        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>This TSI affects vehicles with 1000, 2000, 2000MH and 2400 series Allison transmissions starting
                    10/29/2001 at Allison.
                </para>
                <para>Allison has developed an improved NSBU switch that incorporates a foam seal and a splash shield to
                    prevent water intrusion. Water intrusion could cause the engine not to start in neutral or the
                    backup lights not to function.
                </para>
                <para>A soft foam seal has been affixed to the backside of the switch to provide improved splash
                    protection between the NSBU and the transmission case. This foam seal is not a 360&#176; seal as it
                    has a drain opening at the bottom.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0113011" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0113011.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             scalefitheight="192px" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1. Backside of NSBU Showing the Foam Seal</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. FOAM SEAL</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <para>The shape of the NSBU switch has been changed slightly to be compatible with the new splash
                    shield. The splash shield can only be used with the new NSBU switch. The new switch color is tan,
                    compared the to black color of the old switch. The splash shield is a loose part and assembles over
                    the shift selector shaft. It is held in place by the selector shaft lever.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0113012" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0113012.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                             scalefitheight="432px" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2. Exploded View</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. SPLASH SHIELD</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. FOAM SEAL</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="f0113013" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0113013.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3. New Switch, Shield, Typical OEM Selector Shaft Lever, and Nut</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="f0113014" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0113014.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4. New Switch with Shield Installed</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="f0113015" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0113015.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 5. New Switch with Shield, Selector Shaft Lever and Nut Installed</caption>
                </figure>
            </geninfo>
